'''Achard II''' was the [[Italo-Normans|Norman]] count of [[Lecce]] (from before 1133) and [[Ostuni]], both in southern [[Apulia]], in today's southern [[Italy]]. 

He was the son of Count Geoffrey II of Lecce and a descendant of one of the sons of [[Tancred of Hauteville]], [[Geoffrey of Hauteville|Geoffrey]], arrived c. 1054, later count of [[Brindisi]]. His daughter Emma of Lecce (b. ca. 1120; d. 1194) had an affair with [[Roger III, Duke of Apulia|Roger]], [[Duke of Apulia]] (b. 1118; d. 10 May 1148), son of [[Roger II of Sicily]] (b. 22 December 1095; d. 26 February 1154). His grandson, of this relationship, was later his heir and King [[Tancred of Sicily|Tancred]] (b. 1138; d. 20 February 1194).

